         <abstract>
            <p>Among the many explanations offered for the sharp rise in the inflation rate, one--federal budget deficits--is seemingly unknown to Congress and the majority of the voting public. In the last quarter century, every increase in the federal budget deficit has led to an increase in the inflation rate, and every surplus to a decrease.</p>
